## In the world of software, most everything takes longer to implement than you expect. And so it's not uncommon to accomplish less in a fixed amount of time than you hope.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a GOOD outcome for your final project. I.e., what WILL you accomplish no matter what?

A basic chess game that works, and the project has few errors in the game and piece rules of chess.


### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BETTER outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you THINK you can accomplish before the final project's deadline?

A unique chess game with the new frog piece, and the project has little to no errors in the game and piece rules of chess.


### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BEST outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you HOPE to accomplish before the final project's deadline?

A unique chess game with the new frog piece, and the project has no errors at all in the game and piece rules of chess.


## In a paragraph or more, outline your next steps. What new skills will you need to acquire? What topics will you need to research? If working with one of two classmates, who will do what?

First, I will familiarize myself with how to use Pygame. Next, I will begin programming by first setting up the board and positioning of the pieces. Then, I will figure out how to code for the movement rules for each chess piece. I will need to learn the skill of assigning these rules to each piece. I will have to then code for allowing each player to play their turn and allow for one player's piece to take the other's. I will need to do a lot of research on how to allow each player to play their turn and how to code to determine who wins the game and make sure the players cannot make choices that break the rules of chess.
